Alienware is back, and this time, we bought the new Alienware Area-51 2025 edition with the RTX 5080 and an Intel CPU for benchmarks and review. The review includes a full analysis on the thermal performance, noise levels, power consumption, bloatware inspection, and of course, a tear-down of Alienware's assembly quality. This comes after our review of the horribly overpriced Origin pre-built PC, which definitely makes Alienware look better than it probably should. Either way, this is a huge improvement for Alienware, but one which is ultimately blighted by a bent SSD and poor value.
